node.text: From reefs to ridges, explore the beauty of the Philippines through the eyes of the locals. While 2020 has been a year of change for travel, the Philippines is excited to invite local visitors to explore the beautiful islands. The #BDTeam had the pleasure of working with @tourism_phl to highlight beautiful places around the Philippines. The opportunities for exploration are endless-from the Hundred Island National Park in Pangasinan to exploring the Suba and Culili Sand Dunes in Ilocos Norte.

node.text: From exploring the stunning castles of Schloss Drachenburg and Schloss Moritzburg to discovering the astounding natural sites of Zugspitze and Eifel National Park, the German Roamers show us the best hidden gems Germany has to offer with @germanytourism.

node.title: Germany - Where Modern and Magic Merge

node.text:
With an incredibly rich history, being an “Egyptian” can have many facets especially when it comes to creativity. Today, we’re sharing a unique story dedicated to any creative who intends to carve their own path no matter the circumstances. 

“It’s proof that the end product most of the time doesn’t pan out the way you expect it. And its by having expectations that you hinder your potential.” - @matiasderada

Watch this beautiful film on Beautiful Destinations Youtube channel. 🇪🇬

🎥 @matiasderada #BDTeam

Below is how you can take action @world_wildlife 

Tell EPA to VETO the Pebble Mine.

Despite the threat of a mining disaster in Bristol Bay, Pebble Mine permitting has been rushed through at record speed. The final environmental review for Pebble Mine was released on July 23 2020 and the US Army Corps can issue a record of decision and permit the mine after 30 days. Now is the time to make our opposition to Pebble Mine heard. 

Call the EPA Regional Director Chris Hladick and Alaskan Senators Lisa Murkowski and Dan Sullivan and tell them to do everything in their power to push the EPA to veto the Pebble Mine.

The EPA has a responsibility to protect Bristol Bay communities and must veto the Pebble Mine.

Lisa Murkowski 907-271-3735
Dan Sullivan 907-271-5915
Chris Hladick 206-553-1234

Learn more about Pebble Mine’s impact on Bristol Bay: https://www.worldwildlife.org/stories...

🎥: @loganlambert

node.text:
Bristol Bay, one of Alaska’s most treasured natural wonders, is under threat. @world_wildlife 

It’s home to an irreplaceable ecosystem and one of the last salmon strongholds. Not only that, its iconic wildlife has sprung up a sustainable tourism industry which effects thousands of Alaskan livelihoods.

All of this is under threat if the Pebble Mine moves forward. The recent approval of the environmental impact statement has made it clear that our voices need to be heard. 

Nature and people can’t live without fresh water, and Bristol Bay is the lifeblood that sustains every species calling the region home. 

On a recent trip to Alaska, the #BDTeam and WWF Ambassador, @jeremyjauncey, learned firsthand about the conservation community’s fight against Pebble Mine. 

Team 
@jeremyjauncey  Host 
@loganlambert  Filmmaker & Editor 
@tomfonta  Creative Director 

TAKE ACTION:
Tell EPA to VETO the Pebble Mine.

Despite the threat of a mining disaster in Bristol Bay, Pebble Mine permitting has been rushed through at record speed. The final environmental review for Pebble Mine was released on July 23 2020 and the US Army Corps can issue a record of decision and permit the mine after 30 days. Now is the time to make our opposition to Pebble Mine heard. 

Call the EPA Regional Director Chris Hladick and Alaskan Senators Lisa Murkowski and Dan Sullivan and tell them to do everything in their power to push the EPA to veto the Pebble Mine.

The EPA has a responsibility to protect Bristol Bay communities and must veto the Pebble Mine.

Lisa Murkowski 907-271-3735
Dan Sullivan 907-271-5915
Chris Hladick 206-553-1234

Learn more about Pebble Mine’s impact on Bristol Bay: https://www.worldwildlife.org/stories...

node.text:
COVID-19 has created many challenges across the world. One of the most significant being the need for medical services. @ifema_madrid saw this challenge and stepped up to solve it by turning into a temporary hospital. In coordination with the community of Madrid, Madrid City Council, and armed forces, IFEMA turned exhibition halls into the largest field hospital in the country which had an overwhelmingly positive impact on fighting this virus. Within a day 1,300 beds and 96 ICU stations were set up  and thousands of people with COVID-19 were treated. ❤️ Although IFEMA is not normally associated with providing medical services, it was time to step up and make a difference. ⠀⠀
⠀⠀
📸: @mblazquez83 ⠀⠀
🎥: #BDTeam @cshep ⠀⠀
⠀⠀
#GoingTheExtraMile @wtandtc

node.text: Last September @davide.anzimanni was talking to @nene.travelling about how badly he wanted to book a ticket and fly out somewhere to meet new people, explore, create and have fun. So they decided to go to Capadokya with @riccardomolaro! 😄 Once we can travel again Cappadocia is definitely at the top of our bucket list! Where do you want to visit in the future? And who would you bring with you? Tag them below! (🎥: @davide.anzimanni + @nene.travelling & @riccardomolaro 🎶: @ooyy_music - Melancholy 📍: Cappadocia (Capadokya))

node.text: Pride is looking different this year but we are still excited to celebrate virtually! We have a special love for New York City as it is the home base for the #BDTeam. We are reminiscing about Pride celebrations of years past with @visittheusa and @nycgo, and we look forward to spreading love in the streets again soon!  #UnitedStories (In partnership with @VisittheUSA 📍: New York City, USA)

node.title: Remembering WorldPride in New York City

node.text: As New York City starts to open back up, we wanted to take a moment to reflect on the efforts of heroes in the hospitality industry who have been helping our frontline workers. @fsnewyork was the first hotel in New York City to open its door to our frontline workers and provide them with a safe haven to stay during such an uncertain time. They quickly transformed the hotel into a near medical-grade facility. Over 300 medical workers called @fsnewyork home during this time as they were provided rooms free of charge. This allowed them to keep their own families safe as they focused on their work and taking care of patients. ❤️ (🎥: @loganlambert 📸: @loganstrongarms 📍: Four Seasons Hotel New York)

node.title: A Safe Haven for Frontline Workers - Four Seasons Hotel New York

node.text:
Admiring the view with @gossegoss and @roamingpuppers, because life is about enjoying fun adventures with your best pals. 🐶🇳🇴

A fairytale land on earth, the Geiranger Fjord is a UNESCO World Heritage Site offering towering mountain peaks and spectacular waterfalls. There are many sightseeing trips available in the area and a vast range of activities to do like kayaking, rafting, hiking, and cycling. 🍃

What destinations have you been dreaming about lately and is Norway one of them?

📽 @gossegoss 
🐶 @roamingpuppers
📍 Geirangerfjord, Norway
🎶 Edvard Grieg - Morning Peer Gynt Suite No.1

node.text:
A fall of trust with @_daniharris in the most exhilarating bungee jump in New Zealand. 🔥 Who would you dare do this with? 🙌🏼

Located 47 meters (154 feet) above the Waikato River, the AJ Hackett Taupo Bungy & Swing is New Zealand's highest cliff-top bungee jump. You can jump solo or tandem with a friend, and you can also choose to go dry or be dunked in the water! Surely, this is an adrenaline-fuelled experience you'll never forget. 🇳🇿

📽 @_daniharris
📍 AJ Hackett Taupo Bungy & Swing, Taupō, New Zealand
🎶 Calvin Harris - Summer

node.text:
Cliffhanger thrills with @martinschricke and @satori_factory, multidisciplinary professional athletes from the @uprising team having wild fun at the French Alps. 🔥

This mind-blowing footage was shot at the Aiguille de Varan, one of the main peaks of the Sallanches Valley in France. It offers a spectacular view of the Mont Blanc Massif on one side and the Aravis Massif on the other, a backdrop that's fitting for picturesque Wingsuit Base Jumping sessions. 🏔

Do you have stunt and jump location requests for the @uprising team?

📽 @martinschricke @satori_factory 
📍 Aiguille de Varan, France
🎶 Ed Sheeran - Bad Habits

node.text:
The perfect island fantasy via @agirlwhoblooms. 🐎✨ With horses running freely on the shore, this is definitely not your average pool with a view. 😍

This was shot in Sumba Island, a hideaway that lies in eastern Indonesia. From surfing, sightseeing, sunbathing, learning from traditional villages, and appreciating local cuisine, there's plenty of things to see, do, and experience in this lesser-known island gem.

What's your favorite island in Indonesia? 🇮🇩

📽 @agirlwhoblooms
📍 Sumba Island, Indonesia
🎶 Because You Move Me - Tinlicker, Helsloot

node.text:
An afternoon well-spent with @goldenlifeofnoah in New York City. 🐶  If you want to escape the crowded streets and admire the iconic skyline from the water, there are several boat tours in New York you can take. Aboard one of these boats, you can enjoy some fresh air and an incredible perspective of the famous Manhattan skyline. 🛥

What's your favorite way to spend afternoons in NYC? 🗽

📽 @goldenlifeofnoah
📍 New York, USA

node.text:
Daily dose of wonder via @johnderting. 😱 This spectacle was shot above a towering waterfall in Alaska, a state known for its superb natural landscapes. 💦

Due to its distance from the lower 48 states as well as its rugged landscapes and climate, Alaska is thought of as "The Last Frontier" of America. Invigorating waterfalls, vast forests, miles of coastline, grand mountains, and spectacular wildlife—a true Alaskan adventure offers these and so much more.

What was your first thought while watching this? 💭

📽 @johnderting
📍 Alaska, USA
🎶 JG - SilhouWET

node.text:
The most epic kayak ride via @flowmotionaerials with @ctoruski and @headwaterscollective. 🚣‍♂️ Would you be brave enough to kayak down New Zealand’s Sutherland Falls? 🤯

With a tiered plunge and a vertical fall of 580 meters (1,904 feet), Sutherland Falls offers an unparalleled spot for kayaking. If you're planning to visit this mighty waterfall, you must prepare for a challenging yet rewarding hike through the Milford Track, one of New Zealand's most popular trails featuring beautiful and unforgettable mountain landscapes. 🇳🇿

📽 @flowmotionaerials 
🚣‍♂️ @ctoruski
🎬 @headwaterscollective
📍 Sutherland Falls, South Island, New Zealand
🎶 The Geek x Vrv - Lazy Love

Slices of Tokyo via @demas. 🗼 Have you been watching the Tokyo 2020(1) Olympics, and if yes, what are your favorite moments so far? 🏆

This year's Summer Olympics is being held in Tokyo from July 23, 2021 to August 8, 2021, featuring 33 competitions and 339 events held across 42 venues. The Olympics bring together nations from all over the world to celebrate the incredible athletic achievements of humans. A highly-anticipated international delight, the event celebrates camaraderie and friendly competition. 🔥

📸 @demas
📍 Tokyo, Japan

node.text:
Jumping into the weekend like @faayeded via @johnnybbooyy. 💦 Are your weekend plans as thrilling as this or more on the relaxing side? 🤔

Located in sunny California, Lake Tahoe holds plenty of gems in store for adventure seekers, one of its most daring ones being this rope swing with a roughly 90-foot drop down to the water. As always, it's important to practice extreme caution and training for stunts like this. 🔥

🏃‍♂️ @faayeded
📽 @johnnybbooyy 
📍 Lake Tahoe, California, USA
🎶 The Memories - Go Down On You

node.text:
Playful moments via @marysmark. 💦 The killer whale, otherwise known as an orca, inhabit all oceans of the world. While they are most abundant in colder waters like Alaska, Antarctica, and Norway, they are also spotted in tropical and subtropical waters such as in Hawaii, Australia, and the Bahamas.

These powerful whales can range from around 25 to 30 feet in length, often spouting every few seconds while swimming and cruising at the surface, as shown in these creatively merged photos. 🐳

Have you ever spotted an orca in the wild? 🖤

📸 @marysmark
📍  Planet Earth

11 seconds of NYC via @dylanwaalker.🗽 Flashing lights, fast-paced energy, glamorous nightlife, and flashy Broadway shows are just some of the things that make New York City so special. Brimming with verve, the city is one of the most hip and happening places to explore, especially when the sun goes down. 💫

What's your favorite city in the world and why? 🏙

📽 @dylanwaalker 
📍 New York, USA
🎶 Chris Brown & Deorro - Five More Hours

Besides enjoying the beach, venturing into lush forests, and going sightseeing, you can also visit museums, explore charming villages full of local traditions, and engage in a wide range of sports. 🇪🇸
